# Components and shadcn

## Where things live

- **`components/ui/`** — Registry primitives only (shadcn CLI). Uses **base-nova** + **@base-ui/react** where the template does. Config: `components.json`.
- **`components/*.tsx`** — Product/feature UI (marketing, dashboard, auth). Import from `@/components/ui/*` and compose; put **one-off or domain-specific** UI here, not in `ui/`.
- **Inventory** — Table in `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`; after adding a primitive, **append that file** so the team stays in sync.

## Adding a new shared primitive

1. `cd` to the Next app root (folder that contains `components.json`).
2. Run **`npx shadcn@latest add <name>`** (see [shadcn components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components)). Example: `npx shadcn@latest add tooltip`.
3. Accept CLI dependency prompts when offered.
4. Import in feature code: `@/components/ui/<name>` (aliases from `components.json`).
5. Run **`npm run lint`** and **`npm run build`**; fix imports/types.
6. Update **`docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`** UI inventory table with the new file.

**Do not** paste `components/ui` source from random repos or older shadcn versions — styles and Base UI APIs drift. Prefer the CLI for this project’s registry.

## Modifying components

| Goal | Approach |
|------|-----------|
| One screen needs different look | Pass **`className`** (and `cn()`) on the primitive from the **feature** component; keep `ui/` default for everyone else. |
| Same tweak everywhere | Edit **`components/ui/<name>.tsx`** in a **minimal** way: keep **`data-slot`** attributes and Base UI structure so behavior and animations stay consistent. |
| New variant (e.g. button size) | Extend **CVA `variants`** in that `ui/` file if it must be reusable; otherwise use `className` from the caller. |
| Upstream template changed | Re-run **`npx shadcn@latest add <name> --overwrite`** only when you intend to **replace** the file; diff first — you may lose local edits. |

**Avoid** putting business logic, data fetching, or routes inside `components/ui/*`. **Avoid** duplicating a whole primitive in `components/` when `shadcn add` can add it once.

## Styling and tokens

- Primitives default to **semantic** tokens (`bg-card`, `text-foreground`, `ring`, `primary`). Marketing/branding can still use **`var(--studio-*)`** via `className` on primitives or on wrappers.
- Merge classes with **`cn()`** from `@/lib/utils`.

## Patterns

- **Button + `Link`**: `nativeButton={false}` and `render={<Link href="..." />}` (see `marketing-header.tsx`).
- **Icons**: `lucide-react`; consistent `size-*` / `h-* w-*`.

